title: Test
summary: This is a multi-line chart with 2 lines representing Anthracite and bituminous, and Sub-bituminous and lignite. The y axis denotes TEST and the x axis denotes Year.
Overall Anthracite and bituminous is gradually increasing, Sub-bituminous and lignite is gradually decreasing,  throughout the Year
The ranking of the lines from topmost to botommmost is as follows: 1. Anthracite and bituminous, and lastly, 2. Sub-bituminous and lignite.
Overall across the Year, Anthracite and bituminous mostly maintained the highest TEST when compared to others with a mean value of 552768.0, and it peaked at 2016.
Sub-bituminous and lignite mostly had the least TEST with a mean value of 408736.0, which peaked at 2014 with a value of 488332.0.
Sub-bituminous and lignite reported the lowest TEST about 319879.0 in Year 2018
The difference of TEST between Anthracite and bituminous and Sub-bituminous and lignite is greater at Year 2018 compared to the Year 2010.
